, notes, projects (we’ve already got the API connected!)  \n  – **Telegram/Signal** → your main chat interface for voice/text commands  \n\n• **Proactive daily briefings** – Every morning I could push:  \n  – Weather ☔ (via wttr.in)  \n  – Today’s top 3 priorities from Notion  \n  – Quick news digest on topics you care about (tech, AI, science)  \n  – Health snapshots (if you sync Whoop/Garmin later)  \n\n• **Smart home & IoT** – With Home Assistant or Alexa, I could:  \n  – Adjust lights/temp based on your schedule or voice cues  \n  – Notify you when the wash is done, fridge door left open, etc.  \n  – Simple scenes like “Focus Mode” → dim lights, enable Do Not Disturb, play focus playlist  \n\n• **Task & project automation** – Beyond Notion:  \n  – Turn vague ideas into actionable steps (e.g., “build a bot” → research, MVP, testing phases)  \n  – Auto‑create GitHub repos, PRs, and basic CI when you start a new coding project  \n  – Track time spent on tasks and gently nudge if you’re stuck too long  \n\n• **Learning & skill growth** – Since you want to improve prompting and ship faster:  \n  – Curate micro‑tutorials on OpenClaw/OpenCode based on your goals  \n  – Quiz you on concepts you’ve learned (spaced repetition style)  \n  – Suggest mini‑projects that match your current skill level  \n\n• **Voice & hands‑free** – Eventually we could add:  \n  – Wake word detection (via Porcupine or similar)  \n  – Speech‑to‑text for quick notes or commands while you’re cooking/walking  \n  – Text‑to‑speech for reading back emails or summaries  \n\n**Where to start?** Pick one that’ll save you time *today*—maybe the daily briefing or email triage. I’ll help you set it up in under 20 minutes, then we iterate.\n\nWhat feels most essential for your Jarvis to handle first? 🚀"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":22362,"output":844,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23206,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0