{"type":"message","id":"51eb601f","parentId":"81a29400","timestamp":"2026-03-30T11:58:08.290Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to explain all possible commands when they type \"/\". This likely refers to OpenClaw CLI commands. I should explain the available OpenClaw commands. Let me first check what OpenClaw commands are available by running `openclaw help` or checking the documentation. I'll use the exec tool to run the help command.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_125174ac4b754ceda97769a8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw help"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":38469,"output":98,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38567,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774871859673,"responseId":"chatcmpl-92cf4c1f61236f06"}}
{"type":"message","id":"499922dd","parentId":"51eb601f","timestamp":"2026-03-30T11:58:15.297Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_125174ac4b754ceda97769a8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.28 (f9b1079) — I'm the reason your shell history looks like a hacker-movie montage.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --container <name>   Run the CLI inside a running Podman/Docker container\n                       named <name> (default: env OPENCLAW_CONTAINER)\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser              Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts guided\n                       setup.\n  configure            Interactive configuration for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  mcp                  Manage OpenClaw MCP config and channel bridge\n  memory               Search, inspect, and reindex memory files\n  message *            Send, read, and manage messages\n  models *             Discover, scan, and configure models\n  node *               Run and manage the headless node host service\n  nodes *              Manage gateway-owned node pairing and node commands\n  onboard              Interactive onboarding for gateway, workspace, and skills\n  pairing *            Secure DM pairing (approve inbound requests)\n  plugins *            Manage OpenClaw plugins and extensions\n  qr                   Generate iOS pairing QR/setup code\n  reset                Reset local config/state (keeps the CLI installed)\n  sandbox *            Manage sandbox containers for agent isolation\n  secrets *            Secrets runtime reload controls\n  security *           Security tools and local config audits\n  sessions *           List stored conversation sessions\n  setup                Initialize local config and agent workspace\n  skills *             List and inspect available skills\n  status               Show channel health and recent session recipients\n  system *             System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui                  Open a terminal UI connected to the Gateway\n  uninstall            Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update *             Update OpenClaw and inspect update channel status\n  webhooks *           Webhook helpers and integrations\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw models --help\n    Show detailed help for the models command.\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Run summary\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \"Hi\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6997,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.28 (f9b1079) — I'm the reason your shell history looks like a hacker-movie montage.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --container <name>   Run the CLI inside a running Podman/Docker container\n                       named <name> (default: env OPENCLAW_CONTAINER)\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser              Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts guided\n                       setup.\n  configure            Interactive configuration for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  mcp                  Manage OpenClaw MCP config and channel bridge\n  memory               Search, inspect, and reindex memory files\n  message *            Send, read, and manage messages\n  models *             Discover, scan, and configure models\n  node *               Run and manage the headless node host service\n  nodes *              Manage gateway-owned node pairing and node commands\n  onboard              Interactive onboarding for gateway, workspace, and skills\n  pairing *            Secure DM pairing (approve inbound requests)\n  plugins *            Manage OpenClaw plugins and extensions\n  qr                   Generate iOS pairing QR/setup code\n  reset                Reset local config/state (keeps the CLI installed)\n  sandbox *            Manage sandbox containers for agent isolation\n  secrets *            Secrets runtime reload controls\n  security *           Security tools and local config audits\n  sessions *           List stored conversation sessions\n  setup                Initialize local config and agent workspace\n  skills *             List and inspect available skills\n  status               Show channel health and recent session recipients\n  system *             System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui                  Open a terminal UI connected to the Gateway\n  uninstall            Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update *             Update OpenClaw and inspect update channel status\n  webhooks *           Webhook helpers and integrations\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw models --help\n    Show detailed help for the models command.\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Run summary\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \"Hi\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli","cwd":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774871895295}}
{"type":"message","id":"554424d7","parentId":"499922dd","timestamp":"2026-03-30T11:59:06.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to explain the possible commands when the user types \"/\". Looking at the help output, I can see the main commands available. Let me organize them in a clear, readable way for Telegram.\n\nI should explain the most commonly useful commands first, then mention the others. Based on the context of this workspace and what Ivek typically uses, I'll focus on the relevant ones.\n\nLet me craft a helpful","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Here are"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":" response explaining the main command categories.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" the main OpenClaw commands you can use (type `/` followed by the command name):\n\n## 🛠️ **Core Commands**\n- `openclaw agent` - Run an agent turn (talk to me via the gateway)\n- `openclaw message` - Send/manage messages (what we're using now!)\n- `openclaw sessions` - List/view conversation sessions\n- `openclaw memory` - Search/inspect your memory files\n- `openclaw skills` - List and inspect available skills\n\n## 🤖 **Agent & Automation**\n- `openclaw agents` - Manage isolated agents/workspaces\n- `openclaw sessions_spawn` - Start a sub-agent for specific tasks\n- `openclaw cron` - Manage scheduled jobs/automations\n- `openclaw acp` - Agent Control Protocol tools (for advanced agent setups)\n\n## 🌐 **Communication**\n- `openclaw channels` - Manage connected chat platforms (Telegram, etc.)\n- `openclaw directory` - Look up contact/group IDs\n- `openclaw pairing` - Secure DM pairing requests\n\n## 🔧 **System & Tools**\n- `openclaw gateway` - Control the WebSocket gateway service\n- `openclaw browser` - Manage the dedicated browser\n- `openclaw nodes` - Manage node pairing and commands\n- `openclaw docs` - Search the live OpenClaw documentation\n- `openclaw doctor` - Health checks and quick fixes\n- `openclaw models` - Discover and configure AI models\n- `openclaw update` - Update OpenClaw and check update status\n\n## 📁 **Files & Data**\n- `openclaw backup` - Create/verify local backup archives\n- `openclaw config` - Non-interactive config helpers\n- `openclaw configure` - Interactive setup for credentials/channels\n- `openclaw sandbox` - Manage sandbox containers for isolation\n- `openclaw secrets` - Secrets runtime controls\n- `openclaw security` - Security tools and config audits\n\n## 💡 **Pro Tips**\n- Add `--help` after any command to see detailed options (e.g., `openclaw message --help`)\n- Use `--verbose` or `-v` for more detailed output\n- Most commands have subcommands - try `openclaw <command> --help` to explore\n\nFor everyday use, you'll probably use:\n- `message` for chatting with me\n- `memory` to recall past conversations\n- `sessions` to review chat history\n- `skills` to see what I can help with\n\nWant me to explain any specific command in more detail? Or shall we try one out? 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":39646,"output":680,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40326,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774871895299,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b2d662c3ae896b59"}}
