{"type":"message","id":"2dfc860f","parentId":"871b15ea","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:24:17.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user typed \"/dock_telegram\" which isn't a standard OpenClaw command. Looking at the channels help, the available commands are: add, capabilities, help, list, login, logout, logs, remove, resolve, status.\n\n\"dock_telegram\" might be a typo or a custom alias. Perhaps they meant \"openclaw channels login --channel telegram\" or something similar? But they specifically typed \"/dock_telegram\" after the slash.\n\nIn OpenClaw, when you type \"/\" in the chat, it might trigger a command? Actually, in this Telegram interface, the user is sending messages that start with \"/\". The system interprets these as commands? Looking at the initial system prompt, it mentions \"/new\" and \"/reset\" for session control. So \"/\" commands are special session management commands.\n\nBut \"/dock_telegram\" isn't listed in the standard session commands. The user might be trying to dock something to Telegram? Or maybe it's a typo for \"openclaw channels login\" or \"openclaw channels add\"?\n\nLet me check if there's a \"dock\" command anywhere. Search for \"dock\" in the help output? I didn't see it.\n\nPerhaps the user is trying to use a feature from another system? Or maybe they think there's a command to \"dock\" the Telegram channel?\n\nLet me respond by explaining what I can do with Telegram channels, and ask for clarification.\n\nI should also check if there are any custom commands or aliases set up. Let me look at the workspace for any custom scripts or aliases.\n\nBut first, let me respond helpfully.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I see you tried `/dock_telegram` - that isn't a standard OpenClaw command. For managing your Telegram channel connection, here are the available options:\n\n## 📱 **Telegram Channel Management**\nYou can use these commands via the OpenClaw CLI:\n- `openclaw channels list` - See current Telegram status (shows it's configured and enabled)\n- `openclaw channels login --channel telegram` - (Re)login or refresh your Telegram session\n- `openclaw channels status` - Check gateway channel health\n- `openclaw channels logs` - View recent Telegram logs\n\n## 💡 **What I can help with right now**\nSince your Telegram is already configured and enabled (as shown by `channels list`), we're already connected! You're chatting with me via Telegram right now.\n\nIf you're looking to:\n- **Send a message to another chat/group** → I can help you use the `message send` command\n- **Check if messages are coming through** → We can test with a quick message\n- **Manage multiple Telegram accounts** → We could add additional configurations\n\nWhat were you hoping to accomplish with `/dock_telegram`? Were you trying to:\n1. Reconnect/refresh the Telegram link?\n2. Send a message to a specific chat?\n3. Something else entirely?\n\nLet me know and I'll guide you through the right command! 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":40819,"output":636,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41455,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774873436517,"responseId":"chatcmpl-975d9a69933d493d"}}
