that our current Notion setup already serves as a centralized hub for tasks, projects, and notes, which could form the foundation of such a system.\n\nI should provide this information back to the user in a clear, concise way. Let me format it nicely","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's what we discussed"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":" for Telegram.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" for your Jarvis-style copilot:\n\n## 🤖 **Jarvis Core Concept**\nA proactive AI copilot that anticipates your needs and handles everyday tasks across your digital life.\n\n## 🔌 **Key Integrations We Planned**\n- **Communication**: Gmail (summarize/draft replies), Calendar (schedule/conflict alerts)\n- **Knowledge Hub**: Notion (tasks, projects, notes - already connected!)\n- **Chat Interface**: Telegram/Signal (your main command center)\n- **Smart Home**: Home Assistant/Alexa (lighting, temp, notifications, scenes)\n\n## ⚡ **Proactive Features**\n- **Daily Briefings**: Weather, top 3 priorities, news digest, health stats\n- **Project Help**: Break down ideas → GitHub setup → time tracking\n- **Learning Support**: Curated tutorials, quizzes, skill-building mini-projects\n- **Voice Control**: Wake word detection, speech-to-text, text-to-speech\n\n## 📓 **NotebookLM Integration Idea**\nFor seeing your Antigravity builds & learning:\n1. **Use existing Notion DB** as structured knowledge base (I can already query it)\n2. **Build custom skill** mirroring NotebookLM with local LLMs\n3. **Future Google NotebookLM API** integration when available\n4. **Periodic Antigravity exports** to feed knowledge base\n\n## 🚀 **Recommended Starting Point**\nBegin with **daily briefings** or **email triage** for immediate time savings, then expand based on what saves you most time.\n\nWant to pick one piece to build first, or shall we explore another area? 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-12