{"type":"message","id":"8a1dfadf","parentId":"b7f6c777","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:26:56.385Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e03e6847ec1b4de08940de11","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n\n## 🦞 What bbymama Helps With\n\n### 📋 Productivity & Automation\n\n- Email management (summarize, draft replies, clear spam)\n\n- Calendar management (scheduling, reminders, conflict resolution)\n\n- Daily briefings (weather, tasks, trends)\n\n- Task management (Notion, to-do systems)\n\n- Document organization (auto-filing, renaming, categorizing)\n\n### 💻 Developer / Coding\n\n- Vibe coding via Claude Code / Codex\n\n- GitHub management (PRs, reviews, bug fixes)\n\n- Build entire apps from text\n\n- Run coding agents overnight\n\n- Auto-deploy projects\n\n### ⚡ Business Automation\n\n- Email prospecting & follow-ups\n\n- Invoice creation & accounting\n\n- Customer support replies\n\n- Market research & competitor analysis\n\n- Content ideation & drafting\n\n### 🔗 Integration Hub\n\n- Gmail + Calendar + Drive workflows\n\n- Notion database management\n\n- Obsidian \"second brain\"\n\n- Twitter/X monitoring & posting\n\n- Slack / Discord / Telegram coordination\n\n### 👤 Personal Assistant\n\n- Flight price monitoring & booking\n\n- Online shopping & ordering\n\n- Health tracking (Whoop, Garmin)\n\n- Meal planning & grocery lists\n\n- Insurance claims & appointments\n\n### 🏠 Smart Home Control\n\n- Home Assistant integration\n\n- Alexa device control\n\n- IoT device monitoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774873616381}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd86e64e","parentId":"8a1dfadf","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:28:03.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at Ivek's profile, I can see what would be most useful beyond Notion. Let me analyze his needs:\n\nFrom USER.md:\n- Focus Areas: Vibe coding (OpenClaw), Agentic AI (OpenCode), Bot building (Antigravity), Automations\n- 12-Month Goal: First income stream\n- Strengths: Design sense, Pattern recognition, Persistence\n- Growth Areas: Coding fundamentals, Architecture/design, Business skills, Project management\n- Working Style: Balanced: research + action\n- Frustrations: Prompting gaps, Setting up tools instead of shipping\n- What bbymama Helps With: Lists many categories\n\nSo beyond Notion, I should highlight what would be most valuable based on his goals and frustrations.\n\nLet me craft a response that focuses on:\n1. What aligns with his focus areas (coding, AI, bots, automation)\n2. What addresses his frustrations (prompting gaps, shipping vs setup)\n3. What supports his 12-month goal (first income stream)\n4. What leverages his strengths (design, pattern recognition, persistence)\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Based on your profile, here's what would be most useful beyond Notion for your specific needs:\n\n## 🎯 **Top Priorities for Your Goals**\n\n### 1. **Coding & Development Flow** (Addresses frustration + growth areas)\n- **Prompt Improvement Helper**: Real-time feedback on your LLM prompts to bridge that gap\n- **Code Generation & Review**: Vibe coding assistance that teaches fundamentals while shipping\n- **Automated Project Setup**: Skip boilerplate - go straight to building (OpenClaw/OpenCode agents)\n- **Debugging Partner**: Explain errors, suggest fixes, teach architecture patterns\n\n### 2. **Income Stream Experiments** (Directly supports 12-month goal)\n- **Idea Validator**: Quick market research on concepts before building\n- **MVP Builder**: Help ship tiny testable versions fast (your persistence + my speed)\n- **Landing Page Generator**: From description → functional site (leverages design sense)\n- **A/B Test Helper**: Track what works, iterate based on data\n\n### 3. **Bot Building Accelerator** (Antigravity focus)\n- **Template Generator**: Starter bots for common use cases (Discord, Telegram, webhooks)\n- **Integration Helper**: Connect APIs without docs diving (your pattern recognition shines here)\n- **Deployment Automation**: From code → running bot with one command\n- **Monitoring Dashboard**: See bot health, usage, errors at glance\n\n### 4. **Learning & Skill Growth** (Working style: research + action)\n- **Personalized Curriculum**: Based on what you're building, not generic tutorials\n- **Project-Based Challenges**: \"Build X to learn Y\" micro-projects\n- **Concept Explainer**: Break down complex topics (AI models, architecture) simply\n- **Progress Tracking**: Show how your skills compound over time\n\n### 5. **Automation Force Multiplier** (Your automations focus)\n- **Workflow Designer**: Describe what you want automated → get the setup\n- **Maintenance Helper**: Keep automations running, alert when broken\n- **Expansion Ideas**: \"Since you automate X, you could also automate Y...\"\n- **Time Savings Tracker**: Show what automations actually save you weekly\n\n## 🚀 **Immediate Quick Wins**\nGiven you hate setting up instead of shipping:\n\n1. **Today**: I can help you build and deploy a tiny Antigravity bot in <30 mins\n2. **This Week**: Create a simple income experiment (landing page + email capture)\n3. **Ongoing**: Weekly \"ship something\" challenges that teach while producing\n\n## 🔑 **Your Superpowers to Leverage**\n- **Design Sense**: I'll handle code/logic, you make it beautiful/intuitive\n- **Pattern Recognition**: Spot opportunities for automation/bots in daily life\n- **Persistence**: I'll keep you shipping when motivation dips\n- **Balanced Style**: Research just enough, then action - repeat\n\nWhat feels most exciting to start with? A bot project, an income experiment, or leveling up your coding flow? 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":43789,"output":890,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44679,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774873616386,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ac477623ad9d4579"}}
