{"type":"message","id":"b81e600d","parentId":"67df3d78","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:43:13.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to provide the search results to Ivek in a clear, helpful way. The search shows several results about Google Antigravity - it appears to be Google's agent-first IDE/platform. Let me share","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Based on my web"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":" this information with him.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" search, here's what I found about **Antigravity**:\n\n## 🔍 **Search Results for Antigravity Documentation**\n\n### 1. **Google Antigravity Official Docs**\n- **URL**: https://antigravity.google/docs/home\n- **Description**: Google Antigravity is an agentic development platform, evolving the IDE into the agent-first era. It enables developers to operate at a higher, task-oriented level managing agents across workspaces, while retaining a familiar AI IDE experience at its core.\n\n### 2. **Getting Started Guide**\n- **URL**: https://codelabs.developers.google.com/getting-started-google-antigravity\n- **Description**: A codelab that guides you through installing and experiencing the features of Google Antigravity.\n\n### 3. **Complete Tutorial (2026)**\n- **URL**: https://antigravity.codes/tutorial\n- **Description**: Complete Guide to Google Antigravity - Master Agent-First Development in 2026, from installation to building production-ready applications.\n\n### 4. **Antigravity AI Overview**\n- **URL**: https://antigravityai.io/\n- **Description**: Google Antigravity is Google's new agent-first IDE, built as a VS Code-style editor with autonomous AI agents inside. These agents can read your project, edit files, run terminal commands, and even drive a real browser to plan, implement, and verify features end to end.\n\n### 5. **Antigravity.md Resource**\n- **URL**: https://antigravity.md/\n- **Description**: Antigravity is mission control for autonomous coding agents. Google's agent-first IDE fundamentally reimagines software development - you don't write code line-by-line anymore, you orchestrate agents that execute tasks asynchronously.\n\n## 📝 **Key Takeaways**\nAntigravity appears to be **Google's agent-first IDE platform** that:\n- Replaces traditional line-by-line coding with **agent orchestration**\n- Provides **autonomous AI agents** that can handle file edits, terminal commands, and browser automation\n- Operates at a **task-oriented level** rather than manual coding\n- Integrates with familiar AI IDE experiences while adding agent capabilities\n\nThis aligns perfectly with your interest in **agentic AI** and could be a powerful tool for your bot building and automation goals!\n\nWould you like me to:\n1. Fetch any of these documentation pages for more details?\n2. Help you get started with Antigravity based on what we found?\n3. Explore how it might integrate with your existing OpenClaw/OpenCode workflow?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":47395,"output":596,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47991,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774874570307,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8df4f492706d7992"}}
